<h1><em>in memory of</em> @HI{{ni}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @N{{}} <strong>@HI{{ni}} V</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
In the above sentence pattern, <strong>@HI{{ni}}</strong> means "in memory of" or "as a token of".
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ha @KJ{{north^sea^road-way}}no o@KJ{{soil^products}}<strong>ni</strong>
      @KJ{{person^shape}}wo @KJ{{buy}}imashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I bought a doll as a souvenir of the trip to Hokkaido.
  </td> </tr>
</table>      
</ol>

